<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
 <head>
   <meta content='text/html; charset=UTF-8' http-equiv='Content-Type' />
 </head>
 <body>
    <h4><center>Your resignation request has been approved</center></h4>
   <p>
    This is to inform that the resignation request created by  <b><%= @employee_resignation.try(:employee).try(:prefix) %>  <%= @employee_resignation.try(:employee).try(:first_name) %>  <%= @employee_resignation.try(:employee).try(:middle_name) %> </b> <%= @employee_resignation.try(:employee).try(:last_name) %>  on <b> <%= @employee_resignation.try(:resignation_date) %> </b>, has been approved by your reporting manager <b><%= @reporting_master.try(:employee).try(:prefix)%> <%= @reporting_master.try(:employee).try(:first_name)%> <%= @reporting_master.try(:employee).try(:middle_name)%> <%= @reporting_master.try(:employee).try(:last_name)%></b></p>
    <p>As part of the separation process, your resignation has now been sent to the HR Head,</p>

   <p>For further details, kindly contact your reporting manager or the HR Team.</p>

    <h4>Details of the Resignation:-</h4>

    <p>Employee ID:- <%= @employee_resignation.try(:employee).try(:manual_employee_code) %></p>

    <p>Employee Name:- <%= @employee_resignation.try(:employee).try(:prefix) %>  <%= @employee_resignation.try(:employee).try(:first_name) %> <%= @employee_resignation.try(:employee).try(:last_name) %> <%= @employee_resignation.try(:employee).try(:middle_name) %></p>

    <p>Reason of Separation:-  <%= @employee_resignation.try(:reason) %></p>

     <br><br>
    </p>
 </body>
</html>